<p>This paper develops a new method to estimate the divisional valuation of conglomerates. Why we want to look at this problem? We want to estimate divisional tobin’q instead of just standalone tobin’s Q because it gives what kind of different insights?</p>

<p><a href="https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/261970">Lang and Stulz (1994)</a> forms a portfolio of comparable standalone to mimic the performance of conglomerates.</p>

